    "title": "HP India Advisory Limited is Hiring: Full Stack Developer (Principal)",
    "description": "HP India Advisory Limited has an exciting opening for a Full Stack Developer at our Chennai office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout HP India Advisory Limited:\nHP India Advisory Limited is a leading organization in the Remote sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Design, develop and maintain scalable software applications\n• Ensure code security and follow best practices for data protection\n• Write clean, maintainable, and well-documented code\n• Integrate third-party APIs and services\n• Write and execute unit tests and integration tests\n• Deploy and manage applications on cloud platforms like AWS, Azure, or GCP\n• Work with agile methodologies including daily stand-ups and sprint planning\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Bachelor's degree in a relevant field\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Microservices\n• Proficiency in React\n• Proficiency in TensorFlow\n• Proficiency in Java\n• Proficiency in Git\n• Proficiency in TypeScript\n• Proficiency in Rust\n• Proficiency in CI/CD\n\nWork Mode: Remote - Work from anywhere in India\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Flexible working hours\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Learning & development budget\n• Professional development and training programs\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Chennai, Tamil Nadu, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with HP India Advisory Limited!",
